JOHANNESBURG - Festivities have kicked off at the Cape Town City Hall ahead of President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address (Sona) on Thursday. This is the first-ever address outside of the parliamentary precinct after it was gutted by a fire early this year. The event, which marks the opening of Parliament is now being held at the Cape Town City Hall. WATCH: Ramaphosa delivers his State of the Nation Address 